PRIVACY POLICY
Beansprites LLC respects the privacy of its users, both parents and children (referred to as 'you' or 'user' or 'player'). Our motto is that it's important for you to make an informed decision regarding the use of our applications and games. Therefore we have provided our privacy policy which describes our privacy practices while you continue to enjoy and use our games and apps. Please read it carefully as it will help guide you to understand what information we collect if any, and how the information is collected while we are fully committed to following the Google Play Families Policy Practices for the Kids & Family section of the Google Play Store.
The following Data types are what is collected by our games, and details regarding our data practices are available for viewing on the landing pages of the games and apps on the Google Play Store as well.
The following information outlines the Data Safety collection practices that our games and apps collect based on their requirements for collection. We do not collect any information regarding the users precise location. We do not collect your name, email address, mailing address, phone, nor do we collect any information regarding ethnicity, gender, political affiliation, or any other detailed personal information.
Approximate location may be shared for the purpose of App functionality, Analytics, Advertising & Marketing, Fraud Prevention and Security as well as compliance.
The User ID is collected solely for the purpose of app functionality.
Purchase history is collected for Analytics, Advertising and Marketing. We do not collect any credit information other than purchase history.
App Activity is collected for Analytics, Advertising and marketing, Fraud Prevention and Security as well as compliance. This applies both to app interactions and other actions. We do not collect in-app search history, data on installed apps or any other user-generated content.
App info and performance under diagnostics is collected solely for the purpose of app functionality and analytics. We do not collect crash logs or any other app performance data other than described here.
Data on the device and other identifiers may be collected for the use of Advertising or marketing, analytics, app functionality and fraud prevention as well as security and compliance.
This is a general overview of our data and privacy practices. For more information, please visit the Google Play Store and the Apple Appstore for further details on privacy practices and any data collected. Details are disclosed on the description page of the apps under the Data Safety section of the app landing page.
We use the following providers to serve contextual ads inside the apps. These ad networks are part of the Google Play and iTunes Appstore certified ad network program & are restricted from tracking users and serving behavioral ads. On iTunes Appstore, we have disabled IDFA and do not track any data on any of our users for games published under Beansprites LLC on the iTunes Appstore. The information is available and displayed on iTunes regarding our games which do not collect any personal data with IDFA disabled.
KIDOZ does not allow ad tracking according to their terms of service listed in the link provided. Unity ads follows COPPA guidelines and if a checkbox is enabled saying this game is targeted towards users under the age of 13, personalized ads are disabled. Admob displays contextual ads inside the game. This applies to games including, but not limited to School House Cleanup, Mermaid Glitter Cupcake Chef & additional games listed in stores.
KIDOZ: https://kidoz.net/safe_ads_policy/
Unity Ads: https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
Applovin: https://www.applovin.com/privacy/
Google Admob: https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en-US
Our apps may contain advertising banners and users have the ability to close the advertisements and/or purchase an in-app no advertisements pack. All ads are subject to human review for appropriateness. Generally, we use accepted safeguards and security measures in an attempt to secure the data collected is secure and require that third-party ad providers agree to do the same. Despite our best efforts, no security measures are impenetrable.
We may receive your non-personal data indirectly from the third-party ad providers. These third parties do not share your user data and such information is used to support the operation of our apps.
For more information on the use of these third parties, please view the privacy policies through the links provided above.
Our apps may contain, at times, information about our other apps with an external link to those apps on the applicable app store. This link may be found on the main, title screen by clicking “More Games.” Once you click on this link, you will be taken to the developer's app store page.
Our apps may contain In-App Purchase to enable additional content. These In-App Purchases are purchased once, and are found on a secured parent targeted screen. We may make small, inconsequential changes to this policy with or without notice to you, so you're encouraged to review the policy from time to time.
Our apps have been designed with the guidelines of the United States Federal Trade Commission (FTC) in mind, as expressed in the Children's Online Privacy Protection rule (COPPA) and strive to meet all duties and obligations under the rule of law. The rule requires operators of online services, including interactive mobile apps, to provide notice and get parental consent prior to collecting information from children under 13. The Federal Trade Commission works for consumers to prevent fraudulent, deceptive, and unfair business practices and to provide information to help spot, stop, and avoid them. If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy policy, please contact us.